This paper is about off-policy learning algorithms in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the trade-offs between update variance, fixed-point bias, and contraction rate in these algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of these algorithms in large-scale environments, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
